#   WHAT IS A DATABASE?
#   Think of it like an Excel file stored on a server.
#   It has "tables" (sheets) with rows and columns.
#   We use SQL (a simple language) to ask questions like:
#   "Give me all customers who spent more than $100"
#
#   WHAT TOOLS DO WE USE IN PYTHON?
#   - sqlite3    → built-in Python library, no install needed
#                  uses a local file as a database (perfect to learn)
#   - pandas     → turns database results into a table you can work with
#   - sqlalchemy → professional tool to connect to real databases
#                  (PostgreSQL, MySQL, etc.)
#
#   INSTALL WHAT YOU NEED:
#   pip install pandas sqlalchemy
#
